docs.lead_paragraph: A valuable mineral spring has been discovered on the line of the Seaboard Railroad, in Virginia, a few miles beyond Suffolk. A colored man named RALPH NELSON, was digging a well on his own farm when he struck a spout of water, which caused him to get out of the pit immediately.
